solution: Since $17 = \frac{51}{3} < \frac {52}3 < \frac {54}3 = 18$, the floor  of $52/3$ is $17$. The given quantity is thus equal to $$\left \lceil \frac{17}{5/23} \right \rceil = \left \lceil \frac{391}{5} \right \rceil = \left \lceil 78.2 \right. \rceil = \boxed{79}.$$
model_solution:
Step 1: Calculate the value of the floor expression: $\left \lfloor 52/3 \right \rfloor$
$52/3=17.\overline{3}$
$\left \lfloor 17.\overline{3} \right \rfloor=17$
Step 2: Calculate the value of the fraction $\frac{17}{5/23}$
Step 3: Calculate the value of the ceiling expression: $\left \lceil \frac{17}{5/23} \right \rceil$
$\frac{17}{5/23} = \frac{17}{\frac{5}{23}} = \frac{17 \cdot 23}{5} = \frac{391}{5} = 78.2$
$\left \lceil 78.2 \right \rceil = 79$
The final answer is: $\boxed{79}$
